          </li>
          <li></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="subNavigator1">San Francisco Bay Area</div>
      <div class="subNavigator1_a">
        <div>
          <div>
            <p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0556/1253/9040/files/article-20220118-san-francisco-bay-img.jpg?v=1642666782" width="100%" alt=""></p>
            <p>This region is known for its gorgeous views, perfect for taking in on your bike. Many visitors take the time to ride over to the Golden Gate Bridge and then back across the bridge. There are plenty of great restaurants in this area, making it a popular tourist destination.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 33px; color:#141414;">The Pacific Coast Highway</p>
            <p>Riding your electric bike down the Pacific Coast Highway is a great option for those who want to travel. The coastal highway stretches from Oregon to the Mexican border and includes some of the most scenic routes in America. There are more than 1,000 miles of this road, so you'll have plenty of options on where to stop and enjoy the scenery on your way down.</p>
            <p>If you're looking for some fun and exciting stops along the way, try visiting Cannon Beach and Astoria, which offer great restaurants and galleries. For a more relaxing time, head to Manzanita or Seaside. You can also take your bike on a ferry part of the State Park system down to get to Tillamook Bay. This is a great option if you want to get out of traffic and enjoy some peace while still biking with your friends or family members.</p>
            <p>Enjoying cycling doesn't have to be daunting! You can find many destinations perfect for biking around your city or state with an electric bike. Don't wait another minute: Try out these popular destinations today!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subNavigator1">Appalachian Trail</div>
      <div class="subNavigator1_a">
        <div>
          <div>
            <p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0556/1253/9040/files/article-20220118-appalachian-trail-img.jpg?v=1642666782" width="100%" alt=""></p>
            <p>This is one of the most well-known long-distance hikes in the country, and it begins at Springer Mountain in Georgia. The Appalachian Trail stretches for 2,190 miles through 14 states, up to its terminus on Mt. Katahdin in Maine.If you happen to be biking during the winter months, you'll need snow gear. This is an excellent choice if you're looking for a scenic ride with plenty of uphill climbs. It's far less crowded than roads or the highway, so you have more freedom to take your time and enjoy the sights.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subNavigator1">New York City</div>
      <div class="subNavigator1_a">
        <div>
          <div>
            <p>New York City is a great place to bike. It's not just for the tourists anymore! With the introduction of Citi Bikes, New Yorkers have been given another option for getting around town. But there are also plenty of other reasons to ride an electric bike in New York City.</p>
            <p>For starters, biking in New York is incredibly convenient. There are bike lanes on every major avenue, making it possible to bike without having to worry about cars or buses. The city's sidewalks are also wide enough for two bikes to comfortably ride side-by-side, meaning you can enjoy your outings with friends or family.</p>
            <p>Beyond convenience, the scenery is unbeatable on a bike ride through NYC. You'll get panoramic views of iconic landmarks like the Brooklyn Bridge and Statue of Liberty, as well as historic neighborhoods like Greenwich Village and SoHo, which are brimming with pieces of history dating back centuries. Not only will you be able to see some fantastic sights on your bike trip, but you'll feel them too. Biking allows you to experience new places up close and personal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subNavigator1">The Beachfront Route.</div>
      <div class="subNavigator1_a">
        <div>
          <div>
            <p>This is the most difficult of the five routes. It will take you up steep hills and on paths with little to no visibility. The first part of the route will take you to Balboa Pier for ocean views, then on to Crystal Cove State Park, where you'll see some great wildlife. You'll be rewarded with a beautiful view of the Pacific Ocean at Laguna Beach before heading back towards San Diego.</p>
            <p>Have you always wanted to try a bike trip but aren't sure where to start? One of the best ways to find a new cycling destination is looking at a map. Electric bikes are a great way to get around, whether commuting, taking a leisurely ride, or exploring your surroundings. The Bay Area, Pacific Coast Highway, Appalachian Trail, and New York City are excellent destinations for an electric bike ride.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
